The army had initially said it would respect the ruling. Wine has not left his house in the outskirts of the capital, Kampala, since voting in the presidential election 12 days ago. He tweeted that the military was still blocking access to all his visitors. Journalists working for the Daily Monitor newspaper say military and police deployments had been reinforced on the road leading to Wine's residence and checkpoints increased. Two cars carrying journalists heading to home on Monday evening were stopped and ordered to go back. --BBC--